HEADWORD: Siscowet
<hw>Sis"co*wet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF American Indian
origin.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large, fat variety of the
namaycush found in Lake Superior; -- called also
<altname>siskawet</altname>, <altname>siskiwit</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

